import DocsLayout from "../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
---

<DocsLayout
  title="Deployment models"
  description="Choose an explicit repository contract: Dockerfile, Docker Compose, or ready static output."
>
  <section>
    <p class="overline">Detection</p>
    <h2>Priority and validation</h2>
    <p>MyPaas inspects the selected branch in this order:</p>
    <ol class="steps">
      <li>A root <code>docker-compose.yml</code> or <code>compose.yml</code>.</li>
      <li>A root <code>Dockerfile</code>.</li>
      <li>A ready <code>index.html</code> in <code>dist</code>, <code>build</code>, <code>public</code>, or root.</li>
    </ol>
    <p>
      If no supported contract is found, project creation or deployment stops
      with an actionable error. MyPaas does not infer a buildpack or invent a runtime.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Dockerfile mode</h2>
    <p>
      Dockerfile mode builds one application image from the repository root. The
      project needs an application port, which may be inferred from <code>EXPOSE</code>
      or reviewed manually before creation.
    </p>
    <ol class="steps">
      <li>Clone the selected commit into an isolated build workspace.</li>
      <li>Generate the runtime environment file from encrypted project values.</li>
      <li>Build the image and capture build output.</li>
      <li>Start the replacement on a fresh local port with explicit CPU and memory limits.</li>
      <li>Switch the Caddy route only after the replacement starts successfully.</li>
    </ol>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Docker Compose mode</h2>
    <p>
      Compose mode is for an application plus supporting services such as a
      database, cache, broker, or worker. Select the service that should receive public traffic.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Compose Doctor checks build context, required variables, port hints, and unsafe configuration flags.</li>
      <li>MyPaas applies resource limits and the public port through an override file.</li>
      <li>Logs and metrics remain selectable per service.</li>
      <li>Existing Compose resources can be audited and explicitly reset when stale volumes or credentials cause conflicts.</li>
    </ul>
    <aside class="warning"><p>Resetting Compose resources is destructive and remains an explicit owner action.</p></aside>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Static mode</h2>
    <p>
      Static mode publishes output that already exists in the repository. MyPaas
      copies the selected directory atomically and configures Caddy to serve it.
      There is no application container and MyPaas does not run framework build commands.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Failure behavior</h2>
    <p>
      A failed Dockerfile or Compose build does not replace the currently routed
      release. Deployment state, build logs, and the failure message remain available for diagnosis.
    </p>
  </section>
</DocsLayout>
